<item>
            <title>[PIG-4440] Some code samples in documentation use Unicode left/right single quotes, which cause a parse failure.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-4440</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The current Pig documentation contains several code samples that wrap strings as &apos;string&apos;, using the Unicode code points for left single quote (U+2018) and right single quote (U+2019).  This is not valid syntax in a Pig script.  This can cause confusion for new users who are trying to get started by copy-pasting code samples from documentation.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
